Simple FAQ Challenge

This is a beginner-level project from https://www.devchallenges.io/, focused on learning HTML and CSS. Iâ€™m using this challenge to refresh and improve my skills in web development.

Challenge Overview

The goal of this challenge is to build a simple FAQ page with sections displaying frequently asked questions, styled with CSS. The page is responsive and adapts to various screen sizes, ensuring a good user experience across devices.

Technologies Used

- HTML: Used for creating the structure of the FAQ page.
- CSS: Used for styling the page and making it responsive.

Features

- A section for the FAQ title.
- Multiple FAQ sections with questions and answers.
- Use of modern CSS techniques such as box-shadow and border-radius for styling.

Purpose

This project is part of my journey to refresh and strengthen my HTML and CSS skills. It provides hands-on experience with building a simple web page from scratch, applying best practices for styling, and ensuring responsiveness.
